title: Treasury now says it could run out of money June 5, buying time for debt ceiling talks
description: Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen said Friday that the United States will likely have enough reserves to push off a potential debt default until June 5.

title: The tech trade is back, driven by A.I. craze and prospect of a less aggressive Fed
description: The Nasdaq closed out its fifth straight weekly gain and is again outperforming other U.S. indexes as tech stocks are back in favor.

title: JPMorgan Chase cut about 500 technology and operations jobs this week, sources say
description: Like many financial firms, JPMorgan periodically trims staff during the year, even as it hires thousands more workers to fill roles.

title: Marvell shares rocket 25% on earnings beat and 'tremendous' business potential for A.I.
description: Shares of Marvell Technology surged about 25% off the back of quarterly earnings results.

title: OpenAI's Sam Altman reverses threat to cease European operations
description: OpenAI's CEO threatened to cease operations in Europe if regulation expanded, then seemed to reverse his stance saying there are "no plans to leave."

title: Inflation rose 0.4% in April and 4.7% from a year ago, according to key gauge for the Fed
description: The core personal consumption expenditures price index was expected to increase 0.3% in April, according to a Dow Jones estimate.

title: Tech layoffs ravage the teams that fight online misinformation and hate speech
description: Meta, Amazon, Alphabet and Twitter have all drastically reduced the size of their teams focused on trust and safety as the companies cut costs.

title: Fintech firm Klarna halves net loss in first quarter as it races toward profitability
description: The results show that Klarna is making "significant strides" toward profitability on a monthly basis by the second half of 2023, the firm said.

title: French riot police fire tear gas at climate protesters outside TotalEnergies shareholder meeting
description: French police on Friday fired tear gas at climate activists who tried to prevent the annual general meeting of oil giant TotalEnergies.

title: A U.S. recession would be 'good news' for markets, strategist says
description: A U.S. recession may prevent a steep market downturn in the second half of 2023, according to Michael Yoshikami, founder and CEO of Destination Wealth Management.

title: U.S., China's top commerce officials meet to discuss trade concerns
description: The meeting between Secretary of Commerce Gina Raimondo and her Chinese counterpart Wang Wentao marks the first cabinet-level U.S-China exchange in months.

title: China's gambling hub opens $2 billion resort with a giant copy of London's Big Ben
description: Macao — often referred to as the Las Vegas of Asia — has added yet another luxury casino resort to the Cotai Strip. And this time it's a British-themed one.

title: As China and the U.S. redefine geopolitics, Europe faces a win-win situation
description: European officials have preferred to take a softer approach to Beijing than that of the Biden administration.

title: TikTok Shop, a rising threat to Shopee and Lazada in Southeast Asia
description: TikTok Shop poses a threat to e-commerce players such as Shopee and Lazada in Southeast Asia as it pushes aggressively into the region.

title: This Singaporean couple runs a side business preserving dead animals — and it’s bringing in 5 figures a month
description: "Serving animals, whether alive or the dead, is very meaningful to me ... Through taxidermy, I help [pet owners] with their grieving," said Vivian Tham.

title: Elon Musk's brain implant company Neuralink announces FDA approval of in-human clinical study
description: The implant, which Neuralink calls the "Link," aims to help patients with severe paralysis control external technologies using only neural signals.

title: China's travel recovery gets more attention, but India's outbound market is 'booming' even faster
description: India's outbound travel market is growing much faster than any other outbound market in the world, according to Agoda's CEO, Omri Morgenshtern.

title: Even if lawmakers can cut a debt ceiling deal, Jim Cramer says it's too early to get bullish
description: CNBC's Jim Cramer said on Thursday it was too early for investors to get bullish on this market, even if lawmakers can cut a debt ceiling deal.
